     <h2 id="historicalnews2000">2000 news</h2>
     <h3>Monthly growth rate of 250,000 entries per month, or more</h3>
     <p>On <strong>1 February 2000</strong>, we reached one million entries. It is remarkable that the database has doubled in size in just two months; and by the end of<strong> May</strong> we reached two million entries. The database is growing at quarter of a million entries every month. This growth rate continued with over three million entries on the system by the end of <strong>September</strong>. </p>
    <p>By early <strong>November 2000</strong> we reached we reached 3,500,000 entries, a growth rate of about half a million entries per month.</p>
    <p>In June 2000, RootsWeb was acquired by Ancestry, a commercial company in the business of offering pay-to-view family history records, including BMD records. FreeBMD continued to use the RootsWeb server.</p>
   <p> <mark>Move some of what is in the next two paragraphs somewhere else - possible out of place / time - PC. </mark> </p>                        
<p>Recently (2020?) many, or most, of the RootWeb message board and mailing list pages have been moved into their archive pages.</p>
   <h3>System enhancements</h3>
   <p> On <strong>26 October 2000</strong>, a new process was implemented for allocating volunteers to Syndicates; and in response to the demands of our volunteers a "Transcribers Knowledge Base" section was added to the FreeBMD site. A new process was also implemented for allocating volunteers to Syndicates.</p>
   <p>On <strong>18 November 2000</strong>, the re-designed Website was launched, making it easier for users and transcribers to navigate to whatever they want to be.</p>
